-- Ayala Corp. Gains to Four-Year High in Manila on $1.2 Billion Bid Report
-- B y   I a n   S a y s o n
-- 2012-02-06T03:39:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-06/ayala-corp-gains-to-four-year-high-in-manila-on-1-2-billion-bid-report.html
Ayala Corp. (AC)  shares climbed to the
highest in more than four years after the Philippine Daily
Inquirer reported that the company plans to bid for $1.15
billion worth of projects under the government’s so-called
public-private partnership program, citing Managing Director
Eric Francia.  The stock advanced 3.4 percent to 392 pesos at 11:37 a.m.
in  Manila , heading for the highest close since Dec. 28, 2007.
The stock jumped as much as 5 percent earlier. Francia couldn’t
be reached for comment at his office.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
